1.1. "Software": Refers to the proprietary source code, scripts, system architectures, prompt instructions (src/instructions/), configuration templates, and local runtime orchestration layers (.sh/.ps1) under the project name "Azuris" or "Chad Gibiti".

1.2. "Licensor": The original creator and sole intellectual property owner, azizu1012.

1.3. "Commercial Use": Any execution, deployment, or modification of the Software aimed at direct or indirect financial leverage or commercial operations. This explicitly covers:
- Offering the Software as a paid service, sub-hosting, or automated SaaS platform.
- Using the Software within institutional commercial workflows or business environments.
- Locking any component, feature, or access code of the Software behind digital paywalls, transactional requirements, or compulsory subscription fees.

1.4. "Authorized Donation": Non-compulsory, voluntary financial contributions processed strictly through the Licensor’s encrypted endpoints (e.g., the built-in /donate architecture). Any external redirection of donations by third-party licensees constitutes a material breach of this Agreement.

1.5. "Dynamic Identity": The technical capability of the Software to dynamically pull and replace core string tokens (e.g., modifying "Chad Gibiti" to runtime bot names via Discord API).

